Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}.

Once your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and stir-fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @Worcester sauce{15%ml} to the mushrooms and allow it to evaporate, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, cook for ~{1%minute} more. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1%300ml carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @water for the sauce{75%ml}. Stir in the lentils, then bring the mixture to the boil. Simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g} and pop it in a #small bowl{} with the @Dijon mustard{10%g} (add less if you don't love mustard) and @creme fraiche{150%g}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then stir together and set aside.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @?butter{1%knob} and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Taste the lentil filling and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

Transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} and top with an even layer of mash.

Spoon the cheese and mustard mixture over the mash and spread it out with the back of a #spoon{}.

Bake the pie on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%minutes}.

When the veggie shepherd's pie is ready, remove from the oven and allow to stand for ~{2%minutes} before serving.

Spoon generously onto your plates and dig in. Enjoy!